   2 Python helper for Semantic Versioning (http://semver.org/)

  19 _REGEX = re.compile(
  20         r"""
  21         ^
  22         (?P<major>(?:0|[1-9][0-9]*))
  23         \.
  24         (?P<minor>(?:0|[1-9][0-9]*))
  25         \.
  26         (?P<patch>(?:0|[1-9][0-9]*))
  27         (\-(?P<prerelease>
  28             (?:0|[1-9A-Za-z-][0-9A-Za-z-]*)
  29             (\.(?:0|[1-9A-Za-z-][0-9A-Za-z-]*))*
  30         ))?
  31         (\+(?P<build>
  32             [0-9A-Za-z-]+
  33             (\.[0-9A-Za-z-]+)*
  34         ))?
  35         $
  36         """, re.VERBOSE)
  37 
  38 _LAST_NUMBER = re.compile(r'(?:[^\d]*(\d+)[^\d]*)+')
  39 
  40 #: Contains the implemented semver.org version of the spec
  41 SEMVER_SPEC_VERSION = "2.0.0"

  44 if not hasattr(__builtins__, 'cmp'):
  45     def cmp(a, b):
  46         return (a > b) - (a < b)

  49 def parse(version):
  50     """Parse version to major, minor, patch, pre-release, build parts.
  51 
  52     :param version: version string
  53     :return: dictionary with the keys 'build', 'major', 'minor', 'patch',
  54              and 'prerelease'. The prerelease or build keys can be None
  55              if not provided
  56     :rtype: dict
  57 
  58     >>> ver = semver.parse('3.4.5-pre.2+build.4')
  59     >>> ver['major']
  60     3
  61     >>> ver['minor']
  62     4
  63     >>> ver['patch']
  64     5
  65     >>> ver['prerelease']
  66     'pre.2'
  67     >>> ver['build']
  68     'build.4'
  69     """
  70     match = _REGEX.match(version)
  71     if match is None:
  72         raise ValueError('%s is not valid SemVer string' % version)
  73 
  74     version_parts = match.groupdict()
  75 
  76     version_parts['major'] = int(version_parts['major'])
  77     version_parts['minor'] = int(version_parts['minor'])
  78     version_parts['patch'] = int(version_parts['patch'])
  79 
  80     return version_parts
  81 
  82 
  83 def comparator(operator):
  84     """ Wrap a VersionInfo binary op method in a type-check """
  85     @wraps(operator)
  86     def wrapper(self, other):
  87         comparable_types = (VersionInfo, dict, tuple)
  88         if not isinstance(other, comparable_types):
  89             raise TypeError("other type %r must be in %r"
  90                             % (type(other), comparable_types))
  91         return operator(self, other)
  92     return wrapper

  95 class VersionInfo(object):
  96     """
  97     :param int major: version when you make incompatible API changes.
  98     :param int minor: version when you add functionality in
  99                       a backwards-compatible manner.
 100     :param int patch: version when you make backwards-compatible bug fixes.
 101     :param str prerelease: an optional prerelease string
 102     :param str build: an optional build string
 103     """
 104     __slots__ = ('_major', '_minor', '_patch', '_prerelease', '_build')
 105 
 106     def __init__(self, major, minor=0, patch=0, prerelease=None, build=None):
 107         self._major = int(major)
 108         self._minor = int(minor)
 109         self._patch = int(patch)
 110         self._prerelease = None if prerelease is None else str(prerelease)
 111         self._build = None if build is None else str(build)
 112 
 113     @property
 114     def major(self):
 115         """The major part of a version"""
 116         return self._major
 117 
 118     @major.setter
 119     def major(self, value):
 120         raise AttributeError("attribute 'major' is readonly")
 121 
 122     @property
 123     def minor(self):
 124         """The minor part of a version"""
 125         return self._minor
 126 
 127     @minor.setter
 128     def minor(self, value):
 129         raise AttributeError("attribute 'minor' is readonly")
 130 
 131     @property
 132     def patch(self):
 133         """The patch part of a version"""
 134         return self._patch
 135 
 136     @patch.setter
 137     def patch(self, value):
 138         raise AttributeError("attribute 'patch' is readonly")
 139 
 140     @property
 141     def prerelease(self):
 142         """The prerelease part of a version"""
 143         return self._prerelease
 144 
 145     @prerelease.setter
 146     def prerelease(self, value):
 147         raise AttributeError("attribute 'prerelease' is readonly")
 148 
 149     @property
 150     def build(self):
 151         """The build part of a version"""
 152         return self._build
 153 
 154     @build.setter
 155     def build(self, value):
 156         raise AttributeError("attribute 'build' is readonly")
 157 
 158     def _astuple(self):
 159         return (self.major, self.minor, self.patch,
 160                 self.prerelease, self.build)
 161 
 162     def _asdict(self):
 163         return collections.OrderedDict((
 164             ("major", self.major),
 165             ("minor", self.minor),
 166             ("patch", self.patch),
 167             ("prerelease", self.prerelease),
 168             ("build", self.build)
 169         ))
 170 
 171     def __iter__(self):
 172         """Implement iter(self)."""
 173         # As long as we support Py2.7, we can't use the "yield from" syntax
 174         for v in self._astuple():
 175             yield v
 176 
 177     def bump_major(self):
 178         """Raise the major part of the version, return a new object
 179            but leave self untouched
 180 
 181         :return: new object with the raised major part
 182         :rtype: VersionInfo
 183 
 184         >>> ver = semver.parse_version_info("3.4.5")
 185         >>> ver.bump_major()
 186         VersionInfo(major=4, minor=0, patch=0, prerelease=None, build=None)
 187         """
 188         return parse_version_info(bump_major(str(self)))
 189 
 190     def bump_minor(self):
 191         """Raise the minor part of the version, return a new object
 192            but leave self untouched
 193 
 194         :return: new object with the raised minor part
 195         :rtype: VersionInfo
 196 
 197         >>> ver = semver.parse_version_info("3.4.5")
 198         >>> ver.bump_minor()
 199         VersionInfo(major=3, minor=5, patch=0, prerelease=None, build=None)
 200         """
 201         return parse_version_info(bump_minor(str(self)))
 202 
 203     def bump_patch(self):
 204         """Raise the patch part of the version, return a new object
 205            but leave self untouched
 206 
 207         :return: new object with the raised patch part
 208         :rtype: VersionInfo
 209 
 210         >>> ver = semver.parse_version_info("3.4.5")
 211         >>> ver.bump_patch()
 212         VersionInfo(major=3, minor=4, patch=6, prerelease=None, build=None)
 213         """
 214         return parse_version_info(bump_patch(str(self)))
 215 
 216     def bump_prerelease(self, token='rc'):
 217         """Raise the prerelease part of the version, return a new object
 218            but leave self untouched
 219 
 220         :param token: defaults to 'rc'
 221         :return: new object with the raised prerelease part
 222         :rtype: str
 223 
 224         >>> ver = semver.parse_version_info("3.4.5-rc.1")
 225         >>> ver.bump_prerelease()
 226         VersionInfo(major=3, minor=4, patch=5, prerelease='rc.2', \
 227 build=None)
 228         """
 229         return parse_version_info(bump_prerelease(str(self), token))
 230 
 231     def bump_build(self, token='build'):
 232         """Raise the build part of the version, return a new object
 233            but leave self untouched
 234 
 235         :param token: defaults to 'build'
 236         :return: new object with the raised build part
 237         :rtype: str
 238 
 239         >>> ver = semver.parse_version_info("3.4.5-rc.1+build.9")
 240         >>> ver.bump_build()
 241         VersionInfo(major=3, minor=4, patch=5, prerelease='rc.1', \
 242 build='build.10')
 243         """
 244         return parse_version_info(bump_build(str(self), token))
 245 
 246     @comparator
 247     def __eq__(self, other):
 248         return _compare_by_keys(self._asdict(), _to_dict(other)) == 0
 249 
 250     @comparator
 251     def __ne__(self, other):
 252         return _compare_by_keys(self._asdict(), _to_dict(other)) != 0
 253 
 254     @comparator
 255     def __lt__(self, other):
 256         return _compare_by_keys(self._asdict(), _to_dict(other)) < 0
 257 
 258     @comparator
 259     def __le__(self, other):
 260         return _compare_by_keys(self._asdict(), _to_dict(other)) <= 0
 261 
 262     @comparator
 263     def __gt__(self, other):
 264         return _compare_by_keys(self._asdict(), _to_dict(other)) > 0
 265 
 266     @comparator
 267     def __ge__(self, other):
 268         return _compare_by_keys(self._asdict(), _to_dict(other)) >= 0
 269 
 270     def __repr__(self):
 271         s = ", ".join("%s=%r" % (key, val)
 272                       for key, val in self._asdict().items())
 273         return "%s(%s)" % (type(self).__name__, s)
 274 
 275     def __str__(self):
 276         return format_version(*(self._astuple()))
 277 
 278     def __hash__(self):
 279         return hash(self._astuple())
 280 
 281     @staticmethod
 282     def parse(version):
 283         """Parse version string to a VersionInfo instance.
 284 
 285         :param version: version string
 286         :return: a :class:`semver.VersionInfo` instance
 287         :rtype: :class:`semver.VersionInfo`
 288 
 289         >>> semver.VersionInfo.parse('3.4.5-pre.2+build.4')
 290         VersionInfo(major=3, minor=4, patch=5, \
 291 prerelease='pre.2', build='build.4')
 292         """
 293         return parse_version_info(version)
 294 
 295     def replace(self, **parts):
 296         """Replace one or more parts of a version and return a new
 297           :class:`semver.VersionInfo` object, but leave self untouched
 298 
 299         :param dict parts: the parts to be updated. Valid keys are:
 300           ``major``, ``minor``, ``patch``, ``prerelease``, or ``build``
 301         :return: the new :class:`semver.VersionInfo` object with the changed
 302           parts
 303         :raises: TypeError, if ``parts`` contains invalid keys
 304         """
 305         version = self._asdict()
 306         version.update(parts)
 307         try:
 308             return VersionInfo(**version)
 309         except TypeError:
 310             unknownkeys = set(parts) - set(self._asdict())
 311             error = ("replace() got %d unexpected keyword "
 312                      "argument(s): %s" % (len(unknownkeys),
 313                                           ", ".join(unknownkeys))
 314                      )
 315             raise TypeError(error)
 316 
 317 
 318 def _to_dict(obj):
 319     if isinstance(obj, VersionInfo):
 320         return obj._asdict()
 321     elif isinstance(obj, tuple):
 322         return VersionInfo(*obj)._asdict()
 323     return obj

 326 def parse_version_info(version):
 327     """Parse version string to a VersionInfo instance.
 328 
 329     :param version: version string
 330     :return: a :class:`VersionInfo` instance
 331     :rtype: :class:`VersionInfo`
 332 
 333     >>> version_info = semver.parse_version_info("3.4.5-pre.2+build.4")
 334     >>> version_info.major
 335     3
 336     >>> version_info.minor
 337     4
 338     >>> version_info.patch
 339     5
 340     >>> version_info.prerelease
 341     'pre.2'
 342     >>> version_info.build
 343     'build.4'
 344     """
 345     parts = parse(version)
 346     version_info = VersionInfo(
 347             parts['major'], parts['minor'], parts['patch'],
 348             parts['prerelease'], parts['build'])
 349 
 350     return version_info
 351

 353 def _nat_cmp(a, b):
 354     def convert(text):
 355         return int(text) if re.match('^[0-9]+$', text) else text
 356 
 357     def split_key(key):
 358         return [convert(c) for c in key.split('.')]
 359 
 360     def cmp_prerelease_tag(a, b):
 361         if isinstance(a, int) and isinstance(b, int):
 362             return cmp(a, b)
 363         elif isinstance(a, int):
 364             return -1
 365         elif isinstance(b, int):
 366             return 1
 367         else:
 368             return cmp(a, b)
 369 
 370     a, b = a or '', b or ''
 371     a_parts, b_parts = split_key(a), split_key(b)
 372     for sub_a, sub_b in zip(a_parts, b_parts):
 373         cmp_result = cmp_prerelease_tag(sub_a, sub_b)
 374         if cmp_result != 0:
 375             return cmp_result
 376     else:
 377         return cmp(len(a), len(b))
 378 
 379 
 380 def _compare_by_keys(d1, d2):
 381     for key in ['major', 'minor', 'patch']:
 382         v = cmp(d1.get(key), d2.get(key))
 383         if v:
 384             return v
 385 
 386     rc1, rc2 = d1.get('prerelease'), d2.get('prerelease')
 387     rccmp = _nat_cmp(rc1, rc2)
 388 
 389     if not rccmp:
 390         return 0
 391     if not rc1:
 392         return 1
 393     elif not rc2:
 394         return -1
 395 
 396     return rccmp
 397

 399 def compare(ver1, ver2):
 400     """Compare two versions
 401 
 402     :param ver1: version string 1
 403     :param ver2: version string 2
 404     :return: The return value is negative if ver1 < ver2,
 405              zero if ver1 == ver2 and strictly positive if ver1 > ver2
 406     :rtype: int
 407 
 408     >>> semver.compare("1.0.0", "2.0.0")
 409     -1
 410     >>> semver.compare("2.0.0", "1.0.0")
 411     1
 412     >>> semver.compare("2.0.0", "2.0.0")
 413     0
 414     """
 415 
 416     v1, v2 = parse(ver1), parse(ver2)
 417 
 418     return _compare_by_keys(v1, v2)
 419 
 420 
 421 def match(version, match_expr):
 422     """Compare two versions through a comparison
 423 
 424     :param str version: a version string
 425     :param str match_expr: operator and version; valid operators are
 426           <   smaller than
 427           >   greater than
 428           >=  greator or equal than
 429           <=  smaller or equal than
 430           ==  equal
 431           !=  not equal
 432     :return: True if the expression matches the version, otherwise False
 433     :rtype: bool
 434 
 435     >>> semver.match("2.0.0", ">=1.0.0")
 436     True
 437     >>> semver.match("1.0.0", ">1.0.0")
 438     False
 439     """
 440     prefix = match_expr[:2]
 441     if prefix in ('>=', '<=', '==', '!='):
 442         match_version = match_expr[2:]
 443     elif prefix and prefix[0] in ('>', '<'):
 444         prefix = prefix[0]
 445         match_version = match_expr[1:]
 446     else:
 447         raise ValueError("match_expr parameter should be in format <op><ver>, "
 448                          "where <op> is one of "
 449                          "['<', '>', '==', '<=', '>=', '!=']. "
 450                          "You provided: %r" % match_expr)
 451 
 452     possibilities_dict = {
 453         '>': (1,),
 454         '<': (-1,),
 455         '==': (0,),
 456         '!=': (-1, 1),
 457         '>=': (0, 1),
 458         '<=': (-1, 0)
 459     }
 460 
 461     possibilities = possibilities_dict[prefix]
 462     cmp_res = compare(version, match_version)
 463 
 464     return cmp_res in possibilities
 465

 467 def max_ver(ver1, ver2):
 468     """Returns the greater version of two versions
 469 
 470     :param ver1: version string 1
 471     :param ver2: version string 2
 472     :return: the greater version of the two
 473     :rtype: :class:`VersionInfo`
 474 
 475     >>> semver.max_ver("1.0.0", "2.0.0")
 476     '2.0.0'
 477     """
 478     cmp_res = compare(ver1, ver2)
 479     if cmp_res == 0 or cmp_res == 1:
 480         return ver1
 481     else:
 482         return ver2
 483 
 484 
 485 def min_ver(ver1, ver2):
 486     """Returns the smaller version of two versions
 487 
 488     :param ver1: version string 1
 489     :param ver2: version string 2
 490     :return: the smaller version of the two
 491     :rtype: :class:`VersionInfo`
 492 
 493     >>> semver.min_ver("1.0.0", "2.0.0")
 494     '1.0.0'
 495     """
 496     cmp_res = compare(ver1, ver2)
 497     if cmp_res == 0 or cmp_res == -1:
 498         return ver1
 499     else:
 500         return ver2

 503 def format_version(major, minor, patch, prerelease=None, build=None):
 504     """Format a version according to the Semantic Versioning specification
 505 
 506     :param int major: the required major part of a version
 507     :param int minor: the required minor part of a version
 508     :param int patch: the required patch part of a version
 509     :param str prerelease: the optional prerelease part of a version
 510     :param str build: the optional build part of a version
 511     :return: the formatted string
 512     :rtype: str
 513 
 514     >>> semver.format_version(3, 4, 5, 'pre.2', 'build.4')
 515     '3.4.5-pre.2+build.4'
 516     """
 517     version = "%d.%d.%d" % (major, minor, patch)
 518     if prerelease is not None:
 519         version = version + "-%s" % prerelease
 520 
 521     if build is not None:
 522         version = version + "+%s" % build
 523 
 524     return version
 525 
 526 
 527 def _increment_string(string):
 528     """
 529     Look for the last sequence of number(s) in a string and increment, from:
 530     http://code.activestate.com/recipes/442460-increment-numbers-in-a-string/#c1
 531     """
 532     match = _LAST_NUMBER.search(string)
 533     if match:
 534         next_ = str(int(match.group(1)) + 1)
 535         start, end = match.span(1)
 536         string = string[:max(end - len(next_), start)] + next_ + string[end:]
 537     return string

 540 def bump_major(version):
 541     """Raise the major part of the version
 542 
 543     :param: version string
 544     :return: the raised version string
 545     :rtype: str
 546 
 547     >>> semver.bump_major("3.4.5")
 548     '4.0.0'
 549     """
 550     verinfo = parse(version)
 551     return format_version(verinfo['major'] + 1, 0, 0)

 554 def bump_minor(version):
 555     """Raise the minor part of the version
 556 
 557     :param: version string
 558     :return: the raised version string
 559     :rtype: str
 560 
 561     >>> semver.bump_minor("3.4.5")
 562     '3.5.0'
 563     """
 564     verinfo = parse(version)
 565     return format_version(verinfo['major'], verinfo['minor'] + 1, 0)
 566

 568 def bump_patch(version):
 569     """Raise the patch part of the version
 570 
 571     :param: version string
 572     :return: the raised version string
 573     :rtype: str
 574 
 575     >>> semver.bump_patch("3.4.5")
 576     '3.4.6'
 577     """
 578     verinfo = parse(version)
 579     return format_version(verinfo['major'], verinfo['minor'],
 580                           verinfo['patch'] + 1)

 583 def bump_prerelease(version, token='rc'):
 584     """Raise the prerelease part of the version
 585 
 586     :param version: version string
 587     :param token: defaults to 'rc'
 588     :return: the raised version string
 589     :rtype: str
 590 
 591     >>> semver.bump_prerelease('3.4.5', 'dev')
 592     '3.4.5-dev.1'
 593     """
 594     verinfo = parse(version)
 595     verinfo['prerelease'] = _increment_string(
 596         verinfo['prerelease'] or (token or 'rc') + '.0'
 597     )
 598     return format_version(verinfo['major'], verinfo['minor'], verinfo['patch'],
 599                           verinfo['prerelease'])
 600

 602 def bump_build(version, token='build'):
 603     """Raise the build part of the version
 604 
 605     :param version: version string
 606     :param token: defaults to 'build'
 607     :return: the raised version string
 608     :rtype: str
 609 
 610     >>> semver.bump_build('3.4.5-rc.1+build.9')
 611     '3.4.5-rc.1+build.10'
 612     """
 613     verinfo = parse(version)
 614     verinfo['build'] = _increment_string(
 615         verinfo['build'] or (token or 'build') + '.0'
 616     )
 617     return format_version(verinfo['major'], verinfo['minor'], verinfo['patch'],
 618                           verinfo['prerelease'], verinfo['build'])

 621 def finalize_version(version):
 622     """Remove any prerelease and build metadata from the version
 623 
 624     :param version: version string
 625     :return: the finalized version string
 626     :rtype: str
 627 
 628     >>> semver.finalize_version('1.2.3-rc.5')
 629     '1.2.3'
 630     """
 631     verinfo = parse(version)
 632     return format_version(verinfo['major'], verinfo['minor'], verinfo['patch'])

 635 def createparser():
 636     """Create an :class:`argparse.ArgumentParser` instance
 637 
 638     :return: parser instance
 639     :rtype: :class:`argparse.ArgumentParser`
 640     """
 641     parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=__package__,
 642                                      description=__doc__)
 643     s = parser.add_subparsers()
 644 
 645     # create compare subcommand
 646     parser_compare = s.add_parser("compare",
 647                                   help="Compare two versions"
 648                                   )
 649     parser_compare.set_defaults(which="compare")
 650     parser_compare.add_argument("version1",
 651                                 help="First version"
 652                                 )
 653     parser_compare.add_argument("version2",
 654                                 help="Second version"
 655                                 )
 656 
 657     # create bump subcommand
 658     parser_bump = s.add_parser("bump",
 659                                help="Bumps a version"
 660                                )
 661     parser_bump.set_defaults(which="bump")
 662     sb = parser_bump.add_subparsers(title="Bump commands",
 663                                     dest="bump")
 664 
 665     # Create subparsers for the bump subparser:
 666     for p in (sb.add_parser("major",
 667                             help="Bump the major part of the version"),
 668               sb.add_parser("minor",
 669                             help="Bump the minor part of the version"),
 670               sb.add_parser("patch",
 671                             help="Bump the patch part of the version"),
 672               sb.add_parser("prerelease",
 673                             help="Bump the prerelease part of the version"),
 674               sb.add_parser("build",
 675                             help="Bump the build part of the version")):
 676         p.add_argument("version",
 677                        help="Version to raise"
 678                        )
 679 
 680     return parser

 683 def process(args):
 684     """Process the input from the CLI
 685 
 686     :param args: The parsed arguments
 687     :type args: :class:`argparse.Namespace`
 688     :param parser: the parser instance
 689     :type parser: :class:`argparse.ArgumentParser`
 690     :return: result of the selected action
 691     :rtype: str
 692     """
 693     if args.which == "bump":
 694         maptable = {'major': 'bump_major',
 695                     'minor': 'bump_minor',
 696                     'patch': 'bump_patch',
 697                     'prerelease': 'bump_prerelease',
 698                     'build': 'bump_build',
 699                     }
 700         ver = parse_version_info(args.version)
 701         # get the respective method and call it
 702         func = getattr(ver, maptable[args.bump])
 703         return str(func())
 704 
 705     elif args.which == "compare":
 706         return str(compare(args.version1, args.version2))
 707 
 708 
 709 def main(cliargs=None):
 710     """Entry point for the application script
 711 
 712     :param list cliargs: Arguments to parse or None (=use :class:`sys.argv`)
 713     :return: error code
 714     :rtype: int
 715     """
 716     try:
 717         parser = createparser()
 718         args = parser.parse_args(args=cliargs)
 719         # args.parser = parser
 720         result = process(args)
 721         print(result)
 722         return 0
 723 
 724     except (ValueError, TypeError) as err:
 725         print("ERROR", err, file=sys.stderr)
 726         return 2
 727 
 728 
 729 def replace(version, **parts):
 730     """Replace one or more parts of a version and return the new string
 731 
 732     :param str version: the version string to replace
 733     :param dict parts: the parts to be updated. Valid keys are:
 734       ``major``, ``minor``, ``patch``, ``prerelease``, or ``build``
 735     :return: the replaced version string
 736     :raises: TypeError, if ``parts`` contains invalid keys
 737     :rtype: str
 738 
 739     >>> import semver
 740     >>> semver.replace("1.2.3", major=2, patch=10)
 741     '2.2.10'
 742     """
 743     version = parse_version_info(version)
 744     return str(version.replace(**parts))
